Explanation
- The handler is defined in app/api/cms/admin.py with @admin_api.route("/group/all") (line: admin_api.route("/group/all")). That admin blueprint is registered inside the CMS blueprint with url_prefix="/admin" (app/api/cms/__init__.py), and the CMS blueprint is registered on the application with url_prefix="/cms" (app/__init__.py). Concatenating the prefixes yields /cms + /admin + /group/all â†’ /cms/admin/group/all.
- The route decorator in the code does not specify methods, so it defines the endpoint as a standard GET route. Therefore GET is acceptable.
- Flask/Werkzeug will automatically provide HEAD for routes that have GET handlers, and Flask will provide automatic OPTIONS handling for routes unless explicitly disabled. These behaviors mean HEAD and OPTIONS are acceptable for this endpoint.
- The code does not declare or enable POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, or TRACE for this route, so those methods are not acceptable.
